  "prompt": "What are the entry requirements for the University of Melbourne?",
  "response": "The entry requirements for the University of Melbourne vary depending on the specific course and level of study. Generally, for undergraduate programs, international students typically need:\n\n1. Completion of a secondary school qualification equivalent to the Australian Year 12\n2. Competitive academic results\n3. English language proficiency requirements, such as:\n- IELTS overall score of 6.5 with no band less than 6.0\n- TOEFL internet-based test score of 79 or higher\n- Other recognized English language tests\n\nFor specific course requirements, domestic and international students should:\n- Check the university's official website\n- Review course-specific entry criteria\n- Consider prerequisite subjects\n- Look at specific academic score requirements\n\nPostgraduate entry requirements differ and often require:\n- A relevant undergraduate degree\n- Specific academic grades\n- Professional experience in some cases\n- Additional English language requirements\n\nProspective students are advised to:\n- Contact the University of Melbourne directly\n- Visit their official admissions website\n- Attend information sessions\n- Consult with admissions counselors for personalized guidance",
